<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Honesty</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-10 21:40:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>OMG!  That bear is a PAIN IN THE ARSE to camp!  On a 6-8 hour spawn but the problem is two-fold:  1)  The bear has placeholder (2 roaming ice skellies) and if they pop in the bears place, and they usually do, then you have to wait ANOTHER 8 hours after killing the placeholders!  2)  In the hidden caves is a VERY HIGH LICH (Necro) that roams around with his pet and he WILL kill you if he sees you.  He use to be RED to 50s but I think now he has been changed to high 40s<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bhah</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-16 13:16:19</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>As is was said, this quest is a PAIN!  For the lizard page, try to get a spot in a group in the area known as "4C" (four corners), where the Archon pyramid is located.  It's not a rare drop, but it'll take you some time.  Stack up some FS weapons to sell and some good exp while you're there. 8)  However, the bear, as mentioned, is located in a cave you have to swim under ice to get to in Everfrost (In the North, west fork of the frozen river).  There is a lich that wanders around, level 45 (according to various sources), has a pet and can't be TOUCHED by a level 30-35.  I mean, can NOT be touched!  Can't get ANY damage at ALL with any melee weapon, and FORGET spells!  If he aggroes on you, he will fear you.  If you manage to get away from him, you have to swim out and zone, then stay away from him whenever you can.  The bear spawns 10-20% of the time, and does have Ice Bones as placeholders.  It also drops an Ingot for Cleric armor quest, so if you're around level 25-30, try to get a cleric to camp this with you, as the bear is between 27-33 (heard this from several places).  Went there, died there, returned and never saw it.  Might wanna try binding and hunting nearby, and if you die simply do a "sense animal" in the cave to see if it pops up.  People have spent 30+ hours camping this thing with no results, so don't expect anything.  This is Verant's worst quest armor piece yet, perhaps equal to Grizzleknot Bark.</font></td></tr></table>
